<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Merrill</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Gunnison</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Yarmouth,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-14"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 14, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Steamer Chesapeake hovering along shore east of Shelburne Saturday
                                night; her purser started by land for Halifax. Gunboat passed here
                                last night four o’clock bound east.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>J. M. MERRILL, <hi rend="italic">United States Consular
                                        Agent.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>